:: Start
An adaption of [[Litany In Which Certain Things Are Crossed Out | https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poems/48158/litany-in-which-certain-things-are-crossed-out]] by Richard Siken.
<br>[[Litany1]]
<br>[[Litany2]]


:: Litany1
<<silently>>
<<set _noparty to ["I'm sorry I couldn't come to your party."]>>
<<set _yesparty to ["I'm sorry I came to your party ", "and seduced you ", "and left you bruised and ruined, you poor sad thing."]>>
<<set _die to "You will be alone always and then you will die.">>
<<set _dietime to _die.length * 60 + 'ms'>>
<<set _yespartytime to _yesparty[0].length * 50 + 'ms'>>
<<set _nopartytime to _noparty[0].length * 50 + 'ms'>>
<</silently>>
Every morning the <<linkreplace "maple leaves." t8n>>maple leaves.<br>
<<indent 8 "Every morning another chapter where the hero shifts">><br>
<<indent 3 "from one foot to the other. Every morning the same big">><br>
and little words
    <<linkreplace "all spelling out desire," t8n>>
        all spelling out<br>
        @@#die;display:inline-block;font:courier;text-indent:11em;@@
        <<timed 500ms>>
            <em><<typewriter _die "#die">></em>
        <</timed>><br>
        <<timed _dietime t8n>>
            So maybe I wanted to give you something more than a catalog<br>
            <<indent 2 "of non-definitive acts,">><br>
            something other than the desperation.<br>
